From 918ce02e6b3cb99780dfd6096ba40bd977a66003 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dalcinsuum <dalcinsuum@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 08:05:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Myanmar (my) and Tedim (td) service languages
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three-language services: English (main) | Myanmar | Tedim Chin (Zolai),
selected via tabs on the intake form and locked per session like the
music source.

Pipeline (language threads end-to-end):
- service_sessions.language column (migration) -> intake validation
  (in:en,my,td) -> DispatchServiceJob Redis payload -> Celery workers
- llm_engine: every generator takes language=; Burmese pinned to Myanmar
  Unicode, Tedim anchored to the Zomi Christian register (Pasian, Topa,
  Zeisu, Kha Siangtho); scripture_ref stays English (worker contract)
- bible_api: multi-translation via canonical 66-book index
  (data/books_en.json) — en: BSB (unchanged), my: Judson 1835,
  td: Lai Siangtho 1932; localized scripture headings
- narration: my -> my-MM-NilarNeural (EDGE_TTS_VOICE_MY); td has no
  edge-tts voice so server TTS is skipped (read-along) unless
  EDGE_TTS_VOICE_TD is set

Music:
- my: 852-song dalsuum/myanmar-hymns library (cleaned, mood-tagged,
  data/hymns_my.json), sung via Suno customMode, cached per hymn
- td: ZBC Labu Lui library SEEDED at deploy by
  workers/tools/seed_tedim_hymns.py (labusaal.com; not committed —
  gitignored; confirm permission with ZBC for production). Playback:
  YouTube embed of real Tedim singing -> cached Suno render ->
  optional tedimhymn.com MIDI instrumental (seed_tedim_midi.py)

Frontend: IntakeForm three-language tabs, full my/td UI strings,
Padauk/Noto Sans Myanmar fonts. Tedim strings flagged for native review.

Known gaps: crisis intercept + classifier are English-keyword based;
extend with my/td terms before production.
